{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-adcd21d0258e33f9","input":{"filename":"research_literature_mapper_prioritized_action_report.md","title":"Prioritized Action Report for Research Literature Mapper","markdown":"# Prioritized Action Report (Research Literature Mapper)\n\n**Evidence**: Loaded dossier (ID 49‑research‑literature‑mapper) and analyzed recent operational records (3 items, risk/opportunity scores).\n\n## 1. Immediate High‑Impact Action (Urgent)\n- **Record**: 49‑A – *Research literature mapper priority case* (status: **urgent**)\n- **Impact**: 57,533 pts; **Risk**: 6 (score 10), **Opportunity**: 7\n- **Recommended Action**:\n  1. Deploy the clustering pipeline to process the top‑10 pending literature batches.\n  2. Generate a summary map of claims and open questions for each batch.\n  3. Deliver the first draft to the research leadership within 2 days.\n- **Rationale**: Highest impact and opportunity, low‑moderate risk; aligns with the agent’s core mission.\n\n## 2. Resolve Blocked Follow‑up (Medium‑Priority)\n- **Record**: 49‑C – *Research literature mapper blocked follow‑up* (status: **blocked**)\n- **Impact**: 28,339 pts; **Risk**: 4 (score 6), **Opportunity**: 2.8\n- **Blocking Factor**: Requires cross‑functional coordination (e.g., data‑engineering for source ingestion).\n- **Recommended Action**:\n  1. Initiate a brief coordination meeting with the data‑engineering lead (30 min).\n  2. Define a minimal ingestion spec that satisfies the mapper’s input format.\n  3. Pilot the spec on a single source to unblock the workflow.\n- **Rationale**: Removing the block unlocks additional downstream value and reduces risk of stagnation.\n\n## 3. Continue Routine Review (Low‑Priority/Continuous)\n- **Record**: 49‑B – *Research literature mapper routine queue item* (status: **in_review**)\n- **Impact**: 14,537 pts; **Risk**: 2 (score 2), **Opportunity**: 1.5\n- **Recommended Action**:\n  1. Perform a quick quality check of the current mapping outputs.\n  2. Document any minor discrepancies for future improvement.\n  3. Archive the item as complete after verification.\n- **Rationale**: Low risk and modest impact; can be handled in parallel with higher‑priority tasks.\n\n## Summary of Prioritization\n| Priority | Record | Impact | Risk | Opportunity | Status |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 (Urgent) | 49‑A | 57,533 | 6 | 7 | urgent |\n| 2 (Medium) | 49‑C | 28,339 | 4 | 2.8 | blocked |\n| 3 (Low) | 49‑B | 14,537 | 2 | 1.5 | in_review |\n\n**Next Steps**:\n1. Execute actions for Record 49‑A immediately.\n2. Schedule the coordination meeting for Record 49‑C by end‑of‑day.\n3. Complete routine checks for Record 49‑B within the next workday.\n\n*All recommendations are based on the current risk/opportunity scores and status fields; further data may adjust priorities.*"},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":2,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:33:37.884Z"}}
